|YKB                     MONK FIGHTING STYLES
|GKB‾ ‾ ‾ ‾ ‾ ‾ ‾ ‾ ‾ ‾ ‾ ‾ ‾ ‾ ‾ ‾ ‾ ‾ ‾ ‾ ‾ ‾ ‾ ‾ ‾ ‾ ‾ ‾ ‾ ‾ ‾ ‾ ‾ 

|CK0  Monks core ability outside of their skills and spells, are
|CK0  base training in various fighting styles. Many of these styles
|CK0  mimic the behaviours of animals in the wild. And, many skills
|CK0  require that the monk be using a certain style.

|CK0  Many of these styles have various advantages and disadvantages.
|CK0  Some fighting styles are great at offense, some are more
|CK0  defensive postures, some allow you to be more agile on your
|CK0  feet with quick strikes, some allow you to focus on healing.

|CK0  Styles are now more than passive bonuses. Monks build rhythm by
|CK0  chaining the right techniques together. A clean opener builds
|CK0  resonance in that style, and certain follow-up techniques act as
|CK0  finishers when your sequence is correct.

|CK0  As a monk advances, some techniques stop being simple attacks and
|CK0  become bridges. These moves preserve combo momentum while shifting
|CK0  you into a new style, letting Crane open into Monkey control,
|CK0  Monkey feed Snake precision, Snake turn into Tiger violence, and
|CK0  Dragon collapse a multi-style chain into a capstone strike.

|CK0  Normal "mswitch" is still important for setup and discipline, but
|CK0  it is not what creates advanced combo flow. Bridge moves are what
|CK0  let you cross stance lines without dropping momentum.

|CK0  You can watch this flow through your monk monitor. It now reports
|CK0  resonance, active combo tags, and the next legal route the guild
|CK0  believes you are ready to take.

|CK0  The Wooden Man Post training room lets you practice stance flow and
|CK0  combo chains safely. Use "monkhelp training post" for details.

